member.name: M:OutputMgr.Logging.LogReader.ReadNextEntry
member.summary:
Read the next log entry.
If a log file is not open, open one from the log file list and start reading. If we reach the end of a log file, close it and open another from the log file list. If we encounter an encoding error, this means that a 6.1.2 file has been read. Any 6.1.2 files must be opened as ASCII and not Unicode, so close it and reopen it using the correct encoding.
member.returns: TRUE if there are more log entries to process (potentially). FALSE if there are no more log entries to process.

member.name: M:OutputMgr.Logging.LogReader.InitializeLogProcessing
member.summary:
This method has 2 objectives any time the LogReader class is instantiated.
1) Validate the input log folder or log file. If a folder is specified, find all the possible log files that could exist based on the start and end date supplied. Then validate those files to see if they really exist. The end result is a list of log files which really do exist and match the start/end date for the log reader request.
2) Validate the supplied log entry type filter. If none was supplied, then assume that all log entries are to be returned (no filter).
